<p> <strong id="pp36s">Promotion Procedure - 3rd Semester and Higher</strong></p>
<p> At promotion meetings for the&nbsp;<strong>third semester</strong>&nbsp;and above, the promotion committee evaluates a student¡¯s academic record in the context of both academic history and written documentation which the co-ordinator may have received from the student. This documentation clarifies the circumstances that might explain lapses in a student¡¯s academic performance. (For example, lengthy hospitalization during the semester).</p>
<p> At these levels, academic history and extenuating circumstances are considered by the the promotion committee in their application of the following policies:</p>
<p> 1. Any grade of DNC, DNA, or F entered on a student transcript is viewed as "<strong>NOT SUCCESSFUL</strong>" in a subject by the promotion committee.</p>
<p> 2. A student who is&nbsp;<strong>not successful</strong>&nbsp;in two or more professional subjects is evaluated on the basis of past academic history. The promotion committee may recommend one of the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>that the student be placed on academic probation for the next semester</li>
<li>that the student withdraw from the full-time program for up to two semesters,</li>
<li>that the student be withdrawn from the full-time program</li>
<li>that the student be withdrawn from the School of Information &amp; Communications Technology.</li>
</ul>
<p>3. A student may be told to repeat the subject(s) for which the student received the F, DNC, or DNA grade(s) in the previous semester. A second unsuccessful attempt in a professional subject may result in the student being withdrawn from the full-time program.</p>
<p> 4. A student who is&nbsp;<strong>not successful</strong>&nbsp;in two or more professional subjects after being readmitted to the full-time program or who is on academic probation may be withdrawn from the School of Information &amp; Communications Technology.</p>
<p> 5. Student transcripts are reviewed each semester.&nbsp; Upon successful completion of a subject that was previously graded DNC, DNA or F , the unsuccessful grade is moved to a section of the transcript called "Not Applicable to the Current Program".</p>
<p> 6. The President's Honours List is a designation granted to those students who meet ALL of the following conditions in an academic semester:</p>
<ul>
<li>GPA of 4.0 (grades of A or better in all credit courses and SAT grades for any non-credit courses)</li>
<li>Enrollment in first semester English or beyond (if applicable to the program)</li>
<li>A curriculum course load for the designated semester (for example, students affiliated to Semester 1 of CTY must be registered in six (6) subjects and students in Semesters 7 and 8 of BSD must be registered for five (5) subjects).</li>
</ul>
