<p> <strong id="gp">Graduation Procedure</strong></p>
<p>* No student will be eligible to graduate with a Seneca College certificate or diploma if, in more than 30% of the subjects required for graduation, the student has received a"D" grade. For degree programs, no student will be eligble to graduate with an overall Grade Point Average (GPA) lower than "C+" (2.5 out of 4) or with an average in professional subjects lower than "C+" or with an average in non-professional subjects lower than "C" (2 out of 4).</p>
<p>* In accordance with Seneca's Academic Policy mandating full disclosure on student transcripts, the transcript will display&nbsp;<strong>ALL</strong>&nbsp;subjects in which the student was enrolled.</p>
<p>* Students who take a mixture of day and continuing education subjects are advised to successfully complete at least 70% of the total required subjects for graduation during the day in order to be signed off as a day student. Exceptions are evaluated on an individual basis. Please see your coordinator.</p>
<p>* Students who enter the program as direct entry students and are granted conditional advanced standings must successfully complete at least 50% of their subjects as a Seneca student.</p>
<p>* Some FCE (continuing education) subjects that cover the same subject material as a day subject may not be counted towards a student graduation. FCE subjects that do not use the same subject code as the day program should not be considered acceptable until confirmed by a coordinator during the semester you are enrolled in the subject.</p>
<p>* Students are expected to graduate with the program they started with. Any student that takes significantly longer than the six semesters used for an advanced diploma, four semesters for a diploma, eight semesters for a degree or two semesters for a certificate may be required to complete extra subjects that fulfill the current program requirements.</p>
