<p><strong id="ictas">ICT Advanced Standing (ADV) Policy</strong> Deadline for ADV Applications</p>
<p>Requests for ADV must be made prior to the start of the semester in which the subject for which a student is requesting ADV will be on the student’s timetable. For example: first semester students must apply for ADV in first semester subjects no later than the week before the semester starts. Students are advised not to leave requests for ADV until the last moment. Applications for any subject which a student has on their timetable will not be processed until after the second week of the semester if the request is not received prior to the start of the semester.</p>
<p><strong>Process for Transcripts from Canadian Institutions</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>Requests for ADV must include a certified copy of a transcript from an accepted Canadian post-secondary institution. Transcripts from Canadian Universities and public Colleges are acceptable.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Transcripts from private Colleges and commercial certificates may be acceptable. Such transcripts may be accepted without credential evaluation, but will usually require credential evaluation, see below.</p>
<p><strong>Process for Transcripts from Foreign Institutions</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>Requests for ADV based on education at a foreign post-secondary institution require credential evaluation, see below.</p>
<p><strong>Credential Evaluation</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>We accept credential evaluation from ICAS - <a href="http://www.icascanada.ca/home.aspx">http://www.icascanada.ca/home.aspx</a> or WES - <a href="http://www.wes.org/">http://www.wes.org/</a> or CES - <a href="http://learn.utoronto.ca/international-professionals/comparative-education-service-ces">http://learn.utoronto.ca/international-professionals/comparative-education-service-ces</a> <br /> Please keep in mind that it may take a month or more for credential evaluation.</p>
<p><strong>Subject Outlines</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>Requests for ADV must be accompanied by detailed subject outlines in English. Such outlines must be authenticated by either an official stamp with signature from the issuing institution or provision of a URL which links to the subject outline at an institution’s web-site or certification by one of the accepted credential evaluation services, see above.</p>
