<p><strong id="ictinc">ICT – SUP, DEF AND INC Policy</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Supplemental Examination</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p>A grade of SUP is given when a student has completed and passed all requirements and evaluations for a course and failed the final exam. A grade of SUP is given at the discretion of the subject professor and the Promotion Committee. Generally speaking a Professor will consider the grade achieved on a final exam before granting the privilege of a supplemental exam. For example, if a student’s final exam grade is less than 50%, it is not likely that a supplemental exam will be granted. There is a fee charged to write a supplemental exam. Upon passing a supplemental exam the student will be awarded the minimum passing grade for that subject, in most cases a grade of D.</p>
<p><strong>Deferred Examination</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>A deferred exam may be granted, upon request, when a student misses a final exam. A grade of DEF is given at the discretion of the subject professor and the Promotion Committee. There is no fee charged for a deferred examination and the final grade for the subject is calculated in the same manner as if the exam had been written when scheduled. A grade of DEF may be given for compassionate reasons. Compassionate reasons include, but are not limited to – death in the immediate family, unable to travel to the college because of flight cancellation and illness. Valid and verifiable documentation must be provided at the time a student requests a grade of DEF. See the section on Test and Exam Absence Policy.</p>
<p><strong>INC – Incomplete Grade</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>A grade of INC may be granted when a student has not completed a required evaluation item of the course material. A grade of INC is given at the discretion of the subject professor and the Promotion Committee. INC may be granted if a student has failed to complete one assignment or required lab in a course and has satisfactorily completed all other required course evaluations. When a student sees a grade of INC on his transcript it is the responsibility of the student to know which assignment or lab was not completed and complete the required evaluation by the due date given on the student’s transcript. Failure to complete the outstanding work by the due date will result in a grade of F for the subject. If the missing evaluation is submitted by the due date the professor will mark it and change the student’s grade to whatever grade would normally be earned after calculating penalties for late submission of the required evaluation.</p>
